  "texts": [
    "Representation bias occurs when the data set underrepresents or misrepresents specific demographics within the overall population, resulting in a nonrepresentative data set [5].",
    "Evaluation bias is similar to representation bias: it occurs when inappropriate evaluation benchmark data are selected to assess ML models [5].",
    "In this review, this amounted to using the same underrepresentative data sets for training as well as testing the model, which was found to be the case in 7 publications [32][33][34][35][36][37][38].",
    "Aggregation bias occurs when conclusions are drawn based on observations about a larger group, overriding unique characteristics about a smaller demographic within that group [5].",
    "As a result, the data set fails to account for the unique characteristics of more specific demographics within the overall data set."
  ],
